{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>In Eubacteria and some Archaea, the first steps in nucleotide excision repair are carried out by the coordinated action of the UvrA, UvrB, and UvrC proteins. A damage recognition complex composed of 2 UvrA and 2 UvrB subunits scans DNA for abnormalities. Upon binding of the UvrA(2)B(2) complex to a putative damaged site, the DNA wraps around one UvrB monomer. DNA wrap is dependent on ATP binding by UvrB and probably causes local melting of the DNA helix, facilitating insertion of UvrB Î²-hairpin between the DNA strands. Then UvrB probes one DNA strand for the presence of a lesion. If a lesion is found the UvrA subunits dissociate and the UvrB-DNA preincision complex is formed. This complex is subsequently bound by UvrC and the second UvrB is released. If no lesion is found, the DNA wraps around the other UvrB subunit that will check the other stand for damage [[cite:PUB00057848]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>This entry represents the UvrB subunit. UvrB shares structural similarity with helicases and have ATPase activity [[cite:PUB00088371], [cite:PUB00057850]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "3fpn", "name" "Crystal structure of UvrA-UvrB interaction domains"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR027417", "name" "P-loop containing nucleoside triphosphate hydrolase", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR24029" "UVRABC SYSTEM PROTEIN B"}, "hamap" {"MF_00204" "UvrABC system protein B [uvrB]"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR00631" "excinuclease ABC subunit UvrB"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "UvrABC system, subunit B", "short" "UvrB"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 19, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 9324, "taxa" 37536, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 50534, "sets" 0, "proteins" 50533, "structural_models" {"alphaf